rComments: Such a sweet lady and genuinely cares about the well-being of her students (eg. during the pandemic we had check-ins and chats before class). However her teaching is really disorganized, and she makes it very difficult to ace exams; she has very specific grading criteria but questions are vague.

I can see why some students weren't her biggest fans, but this was one of the easiest upper year science classes I've taken. She's not the best lecturer but midterms and exams are fair (but long) and she really cares about her students. She even reweighed our midterms and finals so that you got the best possible grade. I would 100% recommend her.

Dr. S is the most caring prof I've ever had in my 4 years at uOttawa. She genuinely cares about students and explains concepts really well. She answers emails really fast and is always available for questions. Unfortunately someone posted our midterm on Chegg which caused a lot of issues for the other midterm and exam but study and you'll do well

The most unfair class I have ever taken in my 3 years at uOttawa. Her midterm questions are open-ended and often leave room to interpretation, but she expects the most specific answers. She definitely should not teach as even though she comes off as caring, she cannot make a fair exam for the life of her. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS IF ONLINE!!

Extremely kind and understanding and so fun to talk to during office hours. If you don't understand something in class office hours are really helpful for clearing things up. Regularly did mental health check ins at the beginning of lectures. She's a bit of an unsure lecturer but her slides don't have a whole lot to memorize. Tests were really fair

She cares about the grades of her students. Her exams were the best until academic fraud happened; however, she changed the course evaluation where highest exam would weigh 40%. She did this after noticing that students didn't do well when she made the exams harder. I would definitely take her again for an in-person course.

When it comes to actual teaching the course content, DO NOT TAKE. She puts minimal information on her slides and literally reads off the slides with no additional info and no textbook. She is a poor presenter and inconsistent, using filler such as "so... like..." which is very off-putting. I would appreciate getting the content before class but no

This class is very disorganized, after the chegg scandal she made midterm 2 completely unfair in terms of time and number of questions that were asked. I appreciate the amount of quizzes and participation boosts your mark however I find giving us no time for midterm 2 was completely unfair, it was not a good representation of knowledge from class.

She is a caring prof but things went bad when academic fraud happened. Her midterm criteria tends to be very specific even though they're application-based questions... Overall content is really easy though, and it's open-booked. You really need to elaborate a lot in your answers to get full marks and nail every points she wants.

horrible course. took it as an elective and its been the most stressful course i have ever taken. because of someone's academic fraud the whole class got a brutal M2 and the marking was terrible. asked for specific answers on concept based questions. the time limit wasnt enough to cover the whole M2.

This prof is the by far the easiest one I have had. The class is currently online due to Covid but she test us on lecture understanding and not straight memorization like all the other Bio classes. She also is considerate and remarks your midterms appropriately, I went up a 15% from a remark. Good prof, just study the concepts and you'll get an A.
Her midterm 2 are all long answer questions and I couldn't finish it. Everything she tested was on her slides but her exam was too long...

Her marking schemes are ridiculous and are impossible to get a good mark in unless you define every single word you use (even if that isnt specifically asked it the question). Horrible teaching, boring lectures. I would never take her again, seems easy then mark back and what you got wrong is super specific things not in question..

Always helpful, practical and cares a lot about her students and setting them up for success. Midterms reflect her lecture materials, which are very clear, concise and easy to follow. No surprises and always very fair. She knows her stuff.

Slide has either so very few details, or some things that she doesn't go over. Some learning objectives are hard to find in the lectures. Because someone posted MT1 on chegg, MT2 was brutal, all application based no MCQs in 1h20 min, I don't see how everyone should be punished. Class is very vague and stressful. never sure of anything. "Caring"tho
horrible prof

She is not concise at all when lecturing and is rather poor at explaining concepts. Her marking scheme is extremely rigid despite the ambiguity/open-ended nature of her questions. The second midterm was far too long, and not fair at all. I would avoid this prof if I were you.

She seems nice and is probably a great researcher, but really isn't suited to a professor role. The way she lectures makes it hard to pay attention. Her answers to many questions are "watch the 90 minute lecture recording". She frequently has technical errors (that none of my other professors do) that could/should be solved beforehand.

If theres one word for her its phenomenal. She is the best prof ive ever had throughout my years at uottawa. Her lectures are clear and her midterms reflect that material, and theres no surprises. Her kindness literally shines from her, shes understanding and is accessible outside of class. I would so take any other classes she offers.

General Microbiology is obviously a heavy content course as a 2nd year she has done a great job. She is caring about our situations for COVID-19, works well with her TAs to answer everyones questions, always positive, fun, and a diligent personality. Id take more courses with her. She gave us a whole day to prepare for a 2 hour midterm. Easy A!

Loved this class! Fair midterms/final. If u go to class and pay attention u will do well. Also if u dont understand material Dr. Shewaramani is extremely helpful and caring and has no problem going back over concepts that students struggled with. Student success and learning is her top priority. Overall great experience, highly recommend!

Dr. Shewaramani is a new professor. Her lectures are interesting and informative, however, she comes across as uncomfortable and unsure while giving lectures. On exams, make sure to use and define proper terminology in your answers. They are looking for specfic key words, so dont give vauge explanations. Her lecture slides are good study material
